The "Pimm's" Crown (Homemade Cordial)
Origin: Rob Brouse / Good Drinks
Profile: Bitter, Spiced, Fruity, Herbal.
This recipe rejects the pre-made "fruit cup" sodas in favor of a homemade maceration that extracts the medicinal complexity of roots and barks.
The Architecture:
The Cordial: A reduction of orange/lemon/lime peels, Rooibos tea (earthy), Assam tea (tannic), juniper berries, and Gentian Root.
Gentian Root: This is the key. It is the primary bittering agent in Angostura and many amaros. Including it gives the cordial a persistent, back-of-tongue bitterness.
